üåü OOPs Principles ?                                                                        
OOP = Object-Oriented Programming
It focuses on objects, not just functions or logic.
Languages using OOP:
üëâ Java, C++, Python, C#, Kotlin, Swift etc.

‚≠ê Why OOP?
OOP helps you to:
‚úî write clean and readable code
‚úî reuse code easily
‚úî make applications secure
‚úî divide big code into small parts (modularity)
‚úî make code easier to maintain
‚úî model real-world things (like Car, Student, Employee)

üß© There are 4 Main OOP Principles
 Encapsulation
 Inheritance
 Polymorphism
 Abstraction

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 1Ô∏è‚É£ Encapsulation ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What?
Wrapping data (variables) + methods (functions) together into a single unit ‚Üí called Class. 
Why?
‚úî To protect data
‚úî To control who can access what
‚úî To prevent accidental changes
‚úî To make code secure & manageable
üß© Encapsulation Achieved in Two Ways :
   a. Field-level Encapsulation, To protect variables (data):
      ‚úî How to achieve?
               - Make variables private
               - Provide public getters/setters to control access
   b. Method-level Encapsulation, To protect methods (logic):
      ‚úî How to achieve?
                - Use access modifiers to control which methods are visible:
                                                       | Modifier    | Meaning                                     |
                                                       | ----------- | ------------------------------------------- |
                                                       | `private`   | Completely hidden (best for internal logic) |
                                                       | (default)   | Accessible inside same package              |
                                                       | `protected` | Accessible in subclasses                    |
                                                       | `public`    | Accessible by everyone                      |
Note:- isme hum data ko hee hide kr dete hai or apne according decide krte hai acess control.


GETTERS && SETTERS :

1. getters:- it helps to read private things, if that things are public so easly anybody can access like obj.age, syntax int getAge(), here name can be anything
2. setters:- it helps to set private things, syntax void setAge(int age), here name can be anything

Note:- useful situtation like, apke pass requirement hai jisme read-only ya write-only ya 2read-only and 3 write-only class bnao.
